# Error Handling Standards

## Client-Side Error Handling
- Implement global error boundaries for React components
- Create consistent error state UI components
- Use try/catch blocks for async operations
- Log client-side errors to monitoring service

## API Error Handling
- Return consistent error response format from all API endpoints
- Include appropriate HTTP status codes for different error types
- Provide user-friendly error messages suitable for display
- Log detailed error information for debugging

## Form Error Handling
- Display field-level validation errors inline
- Show form-level errors at the top of forms
- Implement proper error focus management for accessibility
- Clear errors appropriately when inputs change

## Error Recovery
- Implement retry mechanisms for transient failures
- Provide user-initiated recovery options where appropriate
- Preserve user input during error recovery
- Document recovery paths for common error scenarios

## Error Monitoring
- Configure error tracking service for production monitoring
- Include relevant context information with error reports
- Set up alerting for critical error conditions
- Implement error categorization for better analysis

